   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE OUTLINE Principles concerning the organization of the church: Being according to life.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Being of the authority of God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Being according to function.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Being according to ministry.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Organization without life being a great mistake Those who serve properly always having the anointing.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Samuel s anointing of David being the best example of a proper appointing of elders.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Two kinds of submission to authority.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Being according to order.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>All problems being the result of not keeping the order.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A summary.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The practice of the organization of the church: The constituents of the church being God mingled with man and man mingled with God.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The universal and local aspects of the church: The definition of these two aspects.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The error of the Roman Catholic Church.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The church not having a headquarters.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The organization of the church having two aspects.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The distinction between offices and gifts: The definition of offices and gifts.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The importance of offices and gifts.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Concerning offices: Apostles: Not being appointed by man.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Being sent by God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The proof of apostleship being the fruit of an apostle s labor.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Being one who submits to God s authority and who is sent by God.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Proving an apostle: 1 Apostles having the authority of God.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>2 Those who are under the work of an apostle needing to submit to his authority.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>3 To submit to an apostle s authority being to accept his apostleship.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Elders and deacons: Those who appoint elders the apostles who submit to the authority of the Holy Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The qualifications of the elders and deacons: 1 Submitting to the authority of the Holy Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>2 Experienced in life.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>3 Having functions.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The appointment of elders and its relationship to the condition of the saints: 1 There must be spiritual saints in order to have spiritual elders.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>2 For the glory and beauty of the church to be manifested, the apostles, elders, and saints all needing to be spiritual.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Concerning gifts: The significance of gifts.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Gifts being a matter of grace: The source of gifts being grace.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>The significance of grace.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The two verses that speak of the relationship between gifts and grace: Two Scripture verses.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Explanations of the two verses: 1 Gifts being obtained according to grace.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>2 Gifts being sustained in grace.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Gifts being also a matter of life and of spirituality.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Conclusion.</S>
   </TEXT>
